{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Criminal offence to use personal email/messaging apps for Govt/Council business",
        "additional_details": "This way Ministers and Local Councillors can be held accountable. It can keep them in check, avoid corruption and stop favouritism regarding awarding contracts.\r\n\r\nIt is an essential law so that those who ask for Freedom of Information can get hold of correspondence when needed. Things can be traced back.",
        "background": "It should be a criminal offence for Local Councillors and those in Government to use their personal emails and messaging apps (including encrypted) for correspondence for official business, including public procurement.",
